race.comment: THE GRUMPY BEAR (2) was in the money at Kilmore first up then met with strong support last time at Ballarat and nothing went right at the business end. He has plenty up his sleeve and is ready to fire on a 7-day return. He can round them up. MORDIALLOC BEACH (11) got too far back at Geelong but was heading in the right direction prior. This is the easiest grade he's contested since his Maiden win and Ben Allen replaces the 3kg apprentice. Has the rail and each way claims. AFFIRMATIVE LAD (1) peaks and is busting to win again. He's also back in grade following a nose defeat here and maps well. They have elected not to claim with McNeil replacing the 3kg apprentice. GO LEFT (12) is in a smart stable and is sure to build on his Maiden win on debut.
